Any one who takes up the only convenient text of the A stronomica which exists——Breiter‘s—will find that Breiter has made the connexion of ideas in this somewhat difficult passage hopelessly obscure by making 686 end a paragraph. By so dividing the passage he has made what is, logically, only a parenthesis (652-86) into the main theme of 643-86. No; the main theme from 643—749 is the dodecatemorie53 and the mention of the functions and powers of quadrata trzgona, &c., is only introduced preparatorily to explaining to the reader that these powers and functions are deducted from by the dodecatemories.
